cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper is about modeling and enhancing routing protocols in VANETs, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the effect of transmission probabilities on average transmission time, which relates to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also evaluates the protocols' performance in terms of packet cost, which is related to control theory (cs.SY) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the security issues in VANETs, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR).
